      <bioghist id="ref3">
         <head>Biographical/Historical note</head>
         <p>Gladys Wells Griffith was the daughter of Nora Stanford Wells and granddaughter of Charles Stanford, brother of Leland Stanford.</p>
      </bioghist>
      <scopecontent id="ref4">
         <head>Scope and Contents note</head>
         <p>Papers consist of Griffith's reminiscences of her relief work after a tornado in Omaha in 1912 and the story of a widow there who remembered Griffith's grandfather Charles Stanford in Schenectady, NY; a photograph of Griffith and Henry Hornbostel, c. 1950; and a note to her son Frank Griffith from George A. Neal, 1963, regarding the reminiscences.</p>
      </scopecontent>
